---
title: Weeknight Fragrant Hoisin Pork Noodles with Carrot, Onion, Green Beans and Peanuts
description: Perfect for a midweek meal, these Weeknight Fragrant Hoisin Pork Noodles can be on your table in less than 25 minutes. Hoisin contains Chinese Five Spice, rice vinegar and red miso which gives it its delicious sweet-umami flavour.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/HF_Y24_R14_W38_UK_QR23495-4_Main_low_2-98139ad0.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/66969a159b6afed05f63f9b1-en-GB.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 808 kcal
  fat: 34.5 g
  saturated fat: 11.4 g
  carbohydrates: 84.4 g
  sugar: 30.8 g
  protein: 39.7 g
  sodium: 6.5 g
  serving size: 471
time required: 25m
author: Lily Stevens
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/weeknight-fragrant-hoisin-pork-noodles-66969a159b6afed05f63f9b1
---

Trim the @carrot{1%unit}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Slice widthways
into pieces about 1/2cm thick.

Halve and peel the @onion{1%unit}. Chop into 2cm chunks.

Crush the @salted peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @British pork mince{240%g}, carrot and onion.

Fry until the mince has browned and the veg has softened, ~{8-10%minutes}.
Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

While the pork and veg cook, boil a full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, trim the @green beans{80%g}, then cut into thirds.

Pour the boiled water into a medium #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring to
a boil. Add the green beans and @egg noodle nest{125%g} and cook until tender,
~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking
together.

Once the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir the @ginger puree{15%g} into the pan and fry until fragrant,
~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @hoisin sauce{30%g}, @ketjap manis{50%g}, @soy sauce{25%ml} and
@water{100%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for amount).

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir the cooked noodles and beans into the sauce.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Share the noodles, pork and veg between your #serving bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the peanuts to finish.

Enjoy!